## Hub vs Consumer Comparison

| Capability | Hub | Consumer |
|-----------|-----|----------|
| AWS resources (DynamoDB, SQS, S3, Lambda, API GW) | Creates and owns | Uses hub's |
| Pipelines | 10 (all agents) | 6 (PR Review, PR Answer, Eval, DevAgent, BugFix, DoD-Fix) |
| WI service hooks | Creates (tag-filtered) | N/A (hub handles) |
| PR Answer hook | Creates (repo-scoped) | Creates (points to hub's Lambda) |
| PR Review policy | Creates | Creates |
| Lambda deployment | `/auto-deploy` | Skipped |
| Lambda env vars | `/auto-lambda-env` | Skipped |
| CloudWatch alarms | `/auto-alarms` | Skipped |
| Cross-repo delegation | Sends to consumers | Receives from hub |
| `/auto-status` dashboard | Full (DLQ, tokens, rates) | N/A |
| `/auto-doctor` scope | Full (files + infra + Lambda) | Files + pipelines only |
